.playwright-mcp/
page-snapshot.md
# Nautilus smoke test runs `python3 -m py_compile` against the
# packaged extension, which drops a __pycache__/ next to the source.
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
# Phase 17 follow-up — VSS COM smoke fixtures regenerated each run by
# `tests/lock_file.ps1` (writes a 4096-byte 0..255 pattern, holds an
# exclusive lock) and the `vss_com_copy_locked_file_via_shadow` test
# (copies the file off the shadow into a sibling restored/ folder).
# Both are reproducible from scratch — no value in tracking.
/tests/vss-test-locked.bin
/tests/vss-test-restored/

# --- Generated tauri assets we don't want in git ---
apps/copythat-ui/src-tauri/Cargo.lock

# --- Strategic docs kept local-only per IP policy ---
# These files stay on disk for in-session reference but are never
# tracked by git. README.md and docs/SECURITY.md are deliberately
# NOT listed here (README.md is rendered by GitHub; SECURITY.md is
# the repo's security-disclosure policy).
/CopyThat2026-Build-Prompts-Guide.md
/CopyThat2026-Build-Prompts-Guide2.md
/CT26.txt
/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
/docs/CHANGELOG.md
/docs/I18N_TODO.md
/docs/ROADMAP.md
/docs/SIGNING_UPGRADE.md
# Phase 18 — user-facing documentation kept local for the 1.0 launch
# rehearsal. Ships only once the public website lands in a separate
# repo / PR (see docs/RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md step "Publish docs site").
/docs/USER_GUIDE.md
/docs/DEVELOPER_GUIDE.md
/docs/FAQ.md
/docs/RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md
/docs/blog/
/docs/site/
/packaging/linux/README.md

# --- Icon workshop scratch output ---
# Per-iteration icon previews (rasterised SVG exports, pre-review
# renders, etc.) live under `/icon-previews/` and are not tracked.
# The approved deliverables live under `/icon/` and ARE tracked.
/icon-previews/
